   <mods:abstract>Jay is glad, so soon after his appointment to office, to begin a
            correspondence with a gentleman who is favorable to the rights of man and a friend of
            the United States. Jay is certain that the enclosed Act of Congress dated 10 December
            1778 will meet with Gerard's approval, and will have salutary consequences. Jay will do
            all in his power to promote harmony between France and the United States. Letterbook
            copy. In Jay's hand.</mods:abstract>
